i bought the 8gb/128gb edition. this is my review after using it for almost 25 days...
Pros

camera is just awesome, especially the nightscape mode. if you like taking pictures or selfies or capturing videos, this phone won't disappoint you.

processor is really nice and fast. also,since it has 8gb ram, it probably won't be lagging for the next couple of years no matter how many apps you use simultaneously.

gaming performance is also pretty good. no issues there

screen and display also has no issues, even under sunlight.

Cons

battery backup is not that good, for me it lasts almost 11-13 hours after almost continuous use of internet, i also play a lot of Pokemon go and use the camera for some time.. after all this battery last 12 hours average. also, i think 8gb ram is another reason for more battery consumption, so battery backup might be better in 6gb edition.

apart from this, I don't think anything else is much of an issue. at this price tag, it is just fine. maybe a software update will help the battery backup issue.

After 1 month usage :
Realme 5 pro 8Gb/128Gb.
[ Earlier used Redmi Note 5 3Gb/32Gb ]

Performance 5/5 : No issues , reason more than sufficient ram and enough memory

Camera 5/5: Having a wide angle lens really helps, I really liked the images and superb Artificial intelligence processing capabilities

Screen 3/5 : Ips LCD so in inside room its good but perform poorly in sunlight which is a disadvantage

Sound 3/5 : Speaker is average, but am really disappointed with audio output, even mediocre phones of redmi can beat this pro mbl in that. Senheizer earphones tested, better with redmi. Their amp is really good.

OS 3/5 : As compared to MIUI, Color Os seemed ordinary. MIUI has lots of many small small features which makes life really convenient in which realme lacks as of now. For example calender app of redmi will automatically download birthdays from facebook which realme mbls doesnot do. etc

Battery 4/5 : Enough battery for 1 day medium usage. Charging is super fast with 20w charger

Got this mbl in 15k.

9. Its inbuilt sound equilizer termed as real sound technology only works with headset.
10. Google assistant works good whereas difficult to handle Alexa.

I was all along a Redme fan. First time gone for Realme and experience so far is reasonably satisfactory. Basis my experience so far, below are key inputs:

Pros:
1. Good Camera - both front and back
2. Battery - Reasonably good ; VOOC fast charger provided which works quite well
3. Look - Nice built ; looks good
4. Size - Perfectly sized ; easy to hold
5. Features - All possible features available except the ones listed under next section
6. Sound - Pretty good
7. Memory - I have 8/128 combo which is much more than enough ; very smooth navigation ; separate Memory card slot makes it bigger
8. Private Safe - This is a great feature to lock private pics, documents, audio ,video files
9. Connectivity - Smooth connection with Bluetooth, WiFi, USB or external devices
10. Screen guard - Phone came with company fitted screen guard
11. Back case - Nice transperant cover provided in package

Improvement Opportunities:
1. Inbuilt App Lock is not available unlike Redme phones. I see it as huge drawback
2. Time stamp on pics feature not available
3. Auto Photo management in Gallery is not up to the mark. Not organized in user friendly manner ; sequencing, segregation, folder placements not optimal
4. No battery charging indicator / light to monitor the progress / completion without touching the phone
5. Screenshot option is Missing. You can take Video of the screen but not pic.

Hope Realme will fix the above issues in upcoming Version updates.

In all, a great buy. Value for Money.

The phone hardware is simply superb!!!
Only the display could have been AMOLED (go for xt if you can)..but I'm not complaining at all.
Otherwise the build quality is good, the battery is good, VOOC charging is superb.
Audio quality on the speaker and handset is excellent, but audio quality thru the headphone jack is ok ok, could have been better.
Display is decent and under direct sunlight performs well.
Rear Camera takes exquisite pics.
The presence of a Wide angle camera gives this phone a great edge.
Selfie camera is decent and does its job well, but won't excite you like the rear camera.
Finger print scanner is fast and accurate, and even the face unlock works like a charm.
Storage with the triple slot gives you enough room to expand to 256GB. (I have the 8/128 variant).
RAM management is well done.
overall hardware of the phone is very good.

The only and only let down you will experience is in the UI. COLOR OS 6.0 seriously is a downgrade for me when I switched from EMUI of Huawei. It feels like a Ferrari being driven around by someone who is just learning to drive.
I just hope that REALME literally dumps COLOR OS and cones up with something similar to OXYGEN OS, when they release the much talked about Realme OS, and hopefully releases it for this model too.
Apart from COLOR OS ruining your experience, the phone is delightful and a breeze to use, go for it without hesitation if the UI is not much of a hassle for you.
Click the like button if this has helped you.

Why buy other phones like redmi note 9 pro max poco x2 etc.. when realme 5 pro is available?
U get literally every thing in this package.
People should stop going behind specs and know what u really want.🥴
My Honest Review after days of usage and research in youtube reviews.
I suggest crystal green variant for a distinct and pleasing look.

BUILD

Let's be honest we all use mobile covers even if it is made of gorilla glass back and front and have glossy glass design.
So it's pointless to waste money on buying fragile glass only to get looks that won't be much visible with the cover on
Glass can break.. but u get a durable plastic back with Realme 5 po and has a beautiful and unique design at the back that looks like glass and give premium looks .(not ultra premium feel ,since it's plastic) ,but plastic back is more practical as i said but still it have a nice close to premium feel too . Plastic is better for connectivity too.
Amazing build quality. Survived drop tests (6 feet) and bend tests both conducted by Gupta tech.

Thickness is 8.9mm vs 8.7mm of poco x2..
0.2mm = 0.02cm i.e not even half the length of 0.1cm (1/5 of 0.1cm) 😂 funny why people find it to argue..

I still pefer notch over any modern camera placements.. it doesn't interrupt the flow of display..
New punch hole setup is irritaing for me.. most users don't like it but they get used to it. But it is a deal breaker for many users like me.
Pop up camera is great for full screen experience.. but durability issues. So notch is still more favorable than these new setups.

DISPLAY - IPS LCD Full HD+ , support widevine l 1 for Netflix stuff

I have Samsung s6 which have superamoled display.
Yes, there's a difference..but IPS LCD is proved to be more visible under direct sunlight + Colors are more accurate and not warm.. amoled have colours overenhanced which is appealing for eyes but at the expense of accuracy.. especially yellow colour.
Amoled is more battery efficient by turning off pixels on dark mode..
At the end amoled may have slight edge on battery that's all.. u can opt for Samsung devices at this price at the expense of performance 🤗.

Color OS 6.0 based on Android 9.0(Pie)

When you buy this device now, u will get a 2.82gb software update. Update it to get color os upgraded to the fullest. and u will get Realme lab option in settings which has dark mode option.
Dark mode can save u a lot of power and keeps the battery efficient for a long time.
But i've heard that people who again updated to Realme UI suffer from Camera quality reduction and battery drainage. So i don't update again for now.
Color OS is a little bulky but it give a lot of customisation options that can satisfy any user.
Pre installed apps can be uninstalled
Also turn off 'Get recommendations' in settings > addition settings and also turn off smart assistant in Smart services option in settings. This makes the UI & battery efficiency greater.

BATTERY : 4035mah ,20w VOOC 3.0 charger

Last for more a day with medium use
Easily last nearly a day with heavy use. ( Around 18-22 hours)
With light use last for many more days.

I recommend to keep the battery% between 30 and 85- 90 for a longer battery life.
Most of the Li ion batteries are efficient upto 300-500 charge cycles.. If u let the phone die(0%) and recharge it back to 100%, the number of charge cycles can reduce more.
For getting 1000-1500 charge cycle never let the battery % drop below 40 and never recharge it above 80% . Especially with fast charging.. battery can degrade quickly. So take care of that.
Currently my rate of drop while using 4g airtel internet + VOLTE and typing this review on Flipkart is 1% per 12 minutes (not excellent but above average)

CAMERA : 48+8+2+2 MP

48 MP primary camera with Sony IMX 586 sensor ( sensor in one plus seven ) is totally satisying
This device gives one of the best possible natural colours with lots of details , sharpness and edge detection in this entire segment.
In terms of natural colours it easily beats 64MP of Redmi note 8 pro. (Refer Trakin Tech on YouTube)
Electronic video stabilization is available but comparatively not up to the mark.

Ultra wide lens reduces the overall quality a bit like any other device in the segment but is useful to capture large areas with decent quality.
Chroma boost can be used if u love enhanced colours over natural.
I suggest opting the natural colours in 5 pro bcos it can be correctly edited later.

Night mode gives great lighting without loss of lot of details but still some details are missing at the edges.
Video recording at night is satisfying for most users but not for camera nerds.
Macro camera is 2MP which capture images correctly only at a distance>/= 4cm and we can't expect a lot from 2MP.
As we know ,practically it is not useful in day to day life but can give some good creative satisfaction needed for many users like me.. but most of the users won't use it in reality but is usable.
So macro lens is not a deal breaker.
Excellent!

Performance +battery efficiency

Color Os is little bit bulky bcos it is feature rich..
So i suggest to u to buy 6/8gb variant for being satisfied even in future when games like pubg can increase its size and memory usage.

Iam a normal PUBG player who plays classic matches for around 4 - 6/7 hours a day. It never heatsup
Snapdragon 712 AIE is simply powerful enough for any heavy pubg gamers (smooth+ultra graphics) who also want to use this device as their primary device for calls and internet. Almost no visible frame drops while playing in Bootcamp with lots of squads around
If u play pro level just buy Poco F1 (SD 845) at this price 😁
There is no need to hesitate!bcos pro gamers require atleast Snapdragon 800+ range chipset.. no need of confusion.
But for players who are still on the way to becoming pro. This device is simply great enough for Smooth + ultra graphics game play.
Even 720g/730g which support extreme settings still need gfx tool to unlock it on budget segement phones..
So what's the difference.?

Battery is lasting me enough for pubg + normal heavy usage of other social media apps.
But people look at battery drain tests in youtube and may become hungry for more power.. but in reality most people don't use the way youtubers use the phone for extreme tests🌀 U will get what u need on this device.
I suggest u to go for 8gb variant if u love to have a high end spec at this price range. (I bought 8gb variant just for an extra satisfaction)

AUDIO QUALITY

It have very loud speakers. But iam not satisfied with the depth of the bass.. it's average .. not much enjoyable
But most people use earphones and u get quality bass and treble.. the vocals are clear.
Call quality is excellent and ur voice is nicely captured by the mic.. it is another problem free area.

Overall Realme 5 pro is a beast with a lot of satisfied practical minded buyers.
For spec lovers.. u may dish out lot of money to buy other devices that are great on paper if u want.. but this device is pure VALUE FOR MONEY : )

For gaming people, the battery lasts a bit less longer( 30~60mins) but it charges from 0 to 100 in half time.
